[[File:Federico Heinz.jpg|thumb|300px|right|Federico Heinz at [[Wikimania|Wikimania 2009]]]]
'''Federico Heinz''' is an [[Argentinian]] [[programmer]] and [[Free Software]] advocate living in [[London]]. He is a co-founder and current president of [[Fundación Vía Libre]], a [[non-profit organization]] that promotes the free flow of knowledge as a motor for social progress, and the use and development of Free Software. He has helped legislators such an Argentina's Ing. Dragan, Dr. Conde, and Peru's [[Edgar Villanueva Nuñez|Dr. Villanueva]] draft and defend legislation demanding the use of Free Software in all areas of [[public administration]].
He works at [[Google]] in their UK office.<ref>https://www.linkedin.com/in/fedeheinz/</ref>
He speaks fluent [[Spanish language|Spanish]], [[English language|English]], and [[German language|German]].
